# ============================================================
# SEERA WEB / MOBILE - Frontend Build Environment
# Copy to .env before building: cp .env.example .env
# ============================================================

# Backend API base URL  (baked in at BUILD time by Vite)
#
# IMPORTANT: the nginx config no longer proxies /api to the backend, so the
# web app must call the API directly. You MUST set this for any real deploy.
#
# - Railway / production web:  REQUIRED → the API service's public URL
#       e.g. VITE_API_BASE_URL=https://seera-api-production.up.railway.app
#   On Railway set it as a BUILD ARG / variable on the WEB service.
#   The frontend appends /api/v1 automatically — do NOT include it here.
#
# - Native APK:  REQUIRED → your backend's public URL (same rule).
#
# - Local dev only: leave EMPTY to use the Vite dev-server proxy / same origin.
#
# Examples:
#   VITE_API_BASE_URL=https://seera-api-production.up.railway.app
#   VITE_API_BASE_URL=http://192.168.1.50:3001     # LAN testing
VITE_API_BASE_URL=
